    <h1>Testimonial & Videos: A Guitarist's Fretting Hand Dystonia Recovery Story</h1>
    <p>This testimonial follows a guitarist's progress through video documentation. The initial clips show involuntary hand clenching when trying to play simple scale runs, followed by retraining sessions showcasing slow, deliberate, splint-assisted exercises.</p>
    
    <p>The final progress video shows complete recovery, with the guitarist executing complex classical pieces effortlessly. The visual proof showcases the effectiveness of motor cortex remapping over months of structured practice.</p>

    <blockquote>
      "Being able to watch the progress videos kept me motivated. Seeing the physical evidence of recovery is incredibly powerful."
    </blockquote>
    
